From my fav shoot this year was this vampire shoot that I shot at fort Tyron. I was still figuring out the overall theme for the book but I knew I wanted to do this vampire shoot and these four would gracious enough to let me shoot them at night with chilly winds. We had outfit changes and make up and fake blood and it came out amazing. You can check out more from this two page spread featuring @zaddy_luu @matthewsblum @therealerikstefan @matteoandrossi in my book Horror Camp!

How could I not mention this fun shoot with these 4. Doing the book I knew I needed a big bad in the woods and then on twitter I saw these AI generated images of Steve Harvey running from monsters in the woods and I knew I had to do that! I sent a call out for someone super tall and I’m so glad it was @jack.ambrose that answered because they went in on the shoot and created the iconic demon look for the book. I couldn’t ask for a better person. The three models we got coincidentally all were named in some variation of Andrew and that was perfect. The spot in the rambles I wanted to use was occupied but lucky for us we found a very dark path with lots of woods and trees. You can see the full 4 page spread in the book Horror Camp. Also at one point I noticed jack’s demon outfit looked like the time tree demon from chainsaw man and I asked him to do the dance and that’s why I edited that video! I love working with other creatives that just get my vision
